Decisions about treating Paget 's disease may be complicated as the disease often affects people differently .
Addison 's disease affects about 0.9 to 1.4 per 10,000 people in the developed world .
Crohn 's disease affects about 3.2 per 1,000 people in Europe and North America .
Paget 's disease affects from 1.5 to 8.0 percent of the population , depending on age and country of residence .
The disease affects men and women equally .
